\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You will (reassuringly, I hope) discover that all of your work is stored as multiple RTF and XML files inside various subfolders. This means that even in the worst possible crash case, if a .scriv file became hopelessly corrupted (although I hope this will never happen), you would still be able to open and edit all of your work in another program that supports RTF files.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 That said, you should }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 not}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  edit the RTF files inside a .scriv package in any other program if you intend to keep using them inside Scrivener, as this may cause problems in Scrivener. Use the }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://67F50977-F38F-4A53-9D05-121373AFC2BB"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Export Files}}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  feature if you want to get your individual files out for use with another program.}}